knc (1.12-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * do a bit more logging by default...
  * Change the default max kids to 128 and document it in knc.1
  * Improve knc.1 to document all env vars that knc sets
  * Fix auto-detection of accepting sockets in inetd-mode.

 -- Roland C. Dowdeswell <roland.dowdeswell@twosigma.com>  Tue, 30 Jul 2019 18:38:05 +0100

knc (1.11-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix a memory leak which provides a unauthentication DoS
  * Add IPv6 address support for env vars and logs
  * Automatically determine if we are a wait service
  * Fix a memory leak in the python bindings
  * default port to the service name (so, ``knc service@host'' works)
  * Fix SIGHUP handling for ``knc -ifw'' to finish the current connexion
  * Don't log when launched program closes STDERR
  * Be more properly aggressive closing fds in the right places
  * Clean up command line options
  * Code cleanup and documentation improvements

 -- Roland C. Dowdeswell <roland.dowdeswell@twosigma.com>  Wed, 30 Aug 2017 18:38:05 +0100

knc (1.10-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Added python support.
  * Fix a few bugs.
  * Added pool and slab allocators for libknc improving performance.
  * Changed knc command line to allow service@host[:port]

 -- Roland C. Dowdeswell <roland.dowdeswell@twosigma.com>  Tue, 19 May 2015 12:38:05 +0100

knc (1.8-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Finish up the API for libknc.  We can almost commit to this, now.
  * Split the debian pkgs up into knc, libknc, and libknc-dev.

